Package com.vector.annotations.publishedapi

Annotations to provide PublishedApi classes for external usage.

See: Description

  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ChangePolicy
    The policy for changes of a types with are marked by a PublishedApi annotation.
    DomainType
    DomainType specifies in which "domain" shall the PublishedApi classes visible and usable.
    VersionType
    VersionType specifies if the annotated field with PublishedApiVersionInfo is a Version or a VersionRange.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    KeepSecretFromPublishedApi
    KeepSecretFromPublishedApi hides the marked method or constructor for the PublishedApi, that a Java client is not able to call the marked element.
    PublishedAllowBreakingChange
    Classes annotated with PublishedAllowBreakingChange are allowed to have a breaking change.
    PublishedApi
    The PublishedApi annotation indicates that the annotated type is part of an published API.
    PublishedApiDomain
    The PublishedApiDomain annotation restricts the visibility of the PublishedApi to a certain API domain.
    PublishedApiVersionCheck
    PublishedApiVersionCheck indicates, that the class required a certain Version of a PublishedApi.
    PublishedApiVersionInfo
    PublishedApiVersionInfo is used to verify a consistent version numbering of the PublishedApi classes.
    PublishedBeta
    The PublishedBeta annotations signifies that a public API (public class, interface, method or field) annotated with PublishedApi is subject to incompatible changes, or even removal, in a future release.
    PublishedField
    Indicates that the annotated field is part of an published type (see PublishedApi for more details), which must not be changed in the development without an approval for the breaking change!
    PublishedMethod
    Indicates that the annotated method is part of an published type (see PublishedApi for more details), which must not be changed in the development without an approval for the breaking change!
    ReworkThisAtNextBreakingChange
    ReworkThisAtNextBreakingChange shall indicate that the annotated element will be reworked/removed at the next PublishedApi breaking change (major version change).
    ReworkThisAtNextPublishedApiChange
    ReworkThisAtNextPublishedApiChange shall indicate that the annotated element will be add or compatible reworked, but not removed at the next possible PublishedApi change (minor version change).
    UsageNotAllowed
    UsageNotAllowed marks a class, that is was exported due to internal compiler dependencies and should never be used in the client code which uses the PublishedApi.
    UsesPublishedApiFrom
    The @UsesPublishedApiFrom marks a method, field or class using PublishedApi from a newer version than the minimal API version.
    UsesPublishedApiFromContainer
    UsesPublishedApiFromContainer defined the container for UsesPublishedApiFrom multiple times at one element.

Package com.vector.annotations.publishedapi Description
